  "title": "🔧 Technician (Manufacturing) | $2970",
  "description": "<p><strong>🔧 Technical Services Technician (Manufacturing) | $2970</strong><br /><em>$2000 - $2500 + Allowance $474 | 3-4days/week</em><br /> </p><p>Looking to build a <strong>hands-on engineering career</strong> in a high-tech manufacturing environment? This role is ideal for candidates who enjoy working with machinery, troubleshooting equipment, and growing their technical skills.<br /><br /><br /> </p><p><strong>⏰ Shift Details</strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>12-hour shift</strong> following a <strong>4-3-3-4 work/rest cycle</strong><br /><em>(Work 4 days → Rest 3 days | Work 3 days → Rest 4 days – repeat)</em></p></li><li><p><strong>Permanent Sunday Night Shift (7.45pm - 7.55am)</strong></p></li></ul><p><br /><br /><strong>💰 Salary & Benefits</strong></p><ul><li><p><strong>Basic Salary:</strong> $2,000 – $2,500</p></li><li><p><strong>Night Shift Allowance:</strong> $334</p></li><li><p><strong>Meal Allowance:</strong> $70</p></li><li><p><strong>Transport Allowance:</strong> $70</p></li><li><p>Stable role with structured training and career development opportunities</p></li></ul><p><br /><br /><strong>💼 Job Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li><p>Operate manufacturing equipment to meet daily production targets</p></li><li><p>Provide technical support and troubleshoot equipment issues to ensure smooth operations</p></li><li><p>Perform daily and monthly preventive maintenance to maintain equipment reliability and efficiency</p></li><li><p>Participate actively in workplace safety initiatives and quality improvement projects</p></li></ul><p><br /><strong>🛠️ Requirements</strong></p><ul><li><p>Minimum <strong>NITEC in any Engineering discipline</strong><br /><em>(Mechanical / Mechatronics / Robotics background preferred)</em></p></li><li><p>Able to read and understand <strong>electrical and mechanical diagrams</strong></p></li><li><p>Comfortable with <strong>12-hour shift work</strong> and overtime</p></li><li><p>Able to <strong>lift 10–15kg</strong></p></li><li><p>Willing to work in a <strong>controlled manufacturing environment</strong></p></li></ul><p><br /><br /><strong>🌟 Why Join?</strong></p><ul><li><p>Exposure to advanced manufacturing technology</p></li><li><p>Hands-on technical learning and skill development</p></li><li><p>Stable shift pattern with predictable rest days</p></li><li><p>Welcoming environment for fresh engineering graduates</p></li><li></li></ul><p><strong>📩 Apply Now</strong><br />Submit your resume to</p><p>📧 Email : <a href=\"mailto:annabelle.koh@crew.sg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">annabelle.koh@crew.sg</a></p><p> 📲 Whatsapp: <a href=\"tel:80882564\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">80882564</a></p><p>Only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</p><p><strong>Annabelle Koh (R25158748)</strong></p><p><strong>Hrnet Ventures Pte Ltd - Crew by Hrnet</strong></p><p><strong>E.A.24C2435</strong></p>",
